The paper proposes a detection method for MIMO channels in communication systems, which falls under the scope of information theory (cs.IT) and communication (cs.COMM). The use of finite alphabets and pulse-amplitude modulation (PAM) symbols suggests a focus on signal processing (cs.SI) and networked systems (cs.NI). Finally, the paper may also touch on machine learning (cs.LG) as it discusses improving detection performance.
